  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed upper floor addition and roof alteration, by reason of their inappropriate design,  siting, scale, massing, bulk, form would create dominant and discordant additions that would overwhelm the characteristic simple form and appearance of the host property, causing harm to the character and appearance of the host property, the wider terrace setting and the visual amenities of the Whistler Street Conservation Area. It would be readily visible and visually intrusive within private views of the site from neighbouring properties on Whistler Street and Battledean Road. The proposed development would be in conflict with the NPPF (2021), Policies PLAN1, DH1 and DH2 of the Islington Strategic and Development Management Policies (2023) and the guidance contained within the Islington Urban Design Guide (2017) and the Whistler Street Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2008). The limited public benefits do not outweigh the less than substantial harm, in conflict with Paragraph 202 of the NPPF (2021)."
